	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello. My name is Mawl. I'm a Troll. When I came into the game I wanted to make a ShadowKnight. <BR>
I went out and tried to find out everythihng I could about what races would be best  for this. <BR>
<BR>
Here&#8217;s what I know. <BR>
<BR>
1. Trolls are stupid. Real stupid. If your gonna be a caster, put all your stat  points into int (for Shadowknight) or Wisdom  for shaman or Strength  (for warrior) . Put the rest wherever, except Charisma &#8211; you&#8217;re never gonna be the prom queen. I suggest agility (it helps you not get hit so much)  <BR>
2. Trolls are strong. You&#8217;re gonna tear the crap out of a lot of things right off the bat. You aren&#8217;t  as strong as an Ogre, so don&#8217;t&#8217;  get the big head. Lets just say you can focus on the fine art of killing at and early age. Go for  armor class items as an SK or warrior, instead of trying to get your strength up. <BR>
3. You&#8217;ve got  an extremely easy starting city.  If you get lost , just check the maps on this site or at EQMAPS.com. One tip &#8211; if you ever fall in the water and you just can&#8217;t  get out. Use the number pad keys and look straight up. Then try it again. I know it sounds stupid. Until you try to buy some meat pies and fall in the pool by the grocer. <BR>
4. A side effect of living by a swamp is you can get your swimming up. Swimming when getting hit by a mob ain&#8217;t fun. Try to pull on land if possible. Swim in your off time.<BR>
5. Regeneration. It&#8217;s what trolls are all about. I love it personally. I&#8217;ve come back from a purple bar.. regenned and killed a mob that almost  had me dead. I&#8217;ve regenned so much in a fight that I&#8217;ve killed a monster and had very little downtime  ( a few seconds) from that fight. This was all at lower levels. In higher levels it will not matter as much. However every little bit helps , right ?  I will tell you something. You can solo if you like downtime. You can group and you will not have so much downtime. Never underestimate having a healer. An SK/shaman duo is really , really nice.  <BR>
6. Your skills (any skills) suck. You  learn slow because you are stupid. I can not emphhasize this enough. If you play a Troll your skills increase at a DRASTICALLY LOWER rate than say, a Halfling or elf.  (Personal rant here, folks &#8211; This gets old really, really fast . I keep dumping points into my weapons skills and at level 20 they are not maxed. NOTHING is maxed.)<BR>
7. You can slam. Whoopee. Sounds like a bonus? It is . We don&#8217;t need shields. (Neither do Ogres BTW) Slam is a skill that does a small amount of damage (depends on skill/level) and has the chance of disrupting a caster type MOB. I can&#8217;t emphasize that enough. You can stop a mob from casting a 500 point Direct damage (DD) spell with the push of one button. That kicks ass. It also means you can use a 2 handed weapon without a shield and still bash. Small races can&#8217;t do that. They have &#8220;bash envy&#8221; <BR>
8. Trolls are KOS (Killed on sight in a great many places.) You&#8217;re either killed because you&#8217;re a Troll or you&#8217;re killed because your choice of deities is not Kosher. In any case don&#8217;t try to stroll around in Freeport at level 10. <BR>
9. Trolls start out in a great spot. There&#8217;s only one exit to the swamp. How easy is that? Kill whatever cons blue. Kobolds are a bit tougher. Personally I leave snakes alone. Snakes poison. Poison is the cause of the death of many a newbie. Kill low stuff (rats/froglock tads/decayed skellys) then try a kobold.  You can move up to Froglocks after that. There are also some tough skeletons and kobold hunters in the North part of the swamp.  This should sustain you until you hit level 8 &#8211; 10.  After that split and head to Ferott or to South Ro. If you feel freaky, run to North Ro and get a Dervish Cutthroat camp. <BR>
10.  Trolls have a good feel to them. This is why I picked a Troll. I know Trolls regen (I also play a cleric and let me tell you I would rather have a regenner than a non regenner in my party.) There is something extremely comforting to a group when a Troll walks up. You get tells like Hey! Big guy! Want to join our group? People equate size with power and it&#8217;s pretty true. I know I feel way more comfortable with a large race in my group. <BR>
11. Trolls scratch a lot. People may find this offensive. What people do not realize is that trolls have very sensitive skin and if it ain&#8217;t swamp air it&#8217;s just not conducive to good skin tone. So we scratch. <BR>
12. Trolls are  a great race to role play. (Sorry  I didn&#8217;t write in &#8220;Troll talk &#8220; here. Troll talk is for the game.  This is a board for god&#8217;s sake) You can make good jokes about Gnome burgers and play the whole &#8220; stupid race&#8221; mindset to the limit if you like (Mawl barsh &#8216;em gud , Boss? ) . I notice some groups like this. (I suggest you drop it if you need clarity in conversation in the group. Some groups are too stupid to understand Troll speak ..LOL. <BR>
13. Trolls can have some really cool names and get away with it - Like &#8220;Mawl&#8221; or FaceRipper&#8221;   for instance. If you  ever see a troll named Butterfly please kill him and put him out of his misery<BR>
14. One thing I&#8217;ve noticed about this area is people keep going on about how great Upper Guk is . Upper Guk is a train station people. If you go there as a level 10  - you will most likely die. Maybe not the first time. But when you get hit by a train of  eight (8 ! )  froggies or more, you will really, really hate Guk.  Come back at 25 + and feel the love though! <BR>
15 Which brings me to my last point. You never, ever want to die as a troll. Because getting EXP sucks so bad. I&#8217;ve heard it&#8217;s better after they removed the restrictions but (as a Troll SK) I can tell you it blows.  I leveled a druid to 17 in less than 2 weeks. I leveled a chanter to level 10 in less than 15 hours. My Troll SK is 20 and it&#8217;s taken an EXTREMELY long  time. However I&#8217;ve got a friend who made 40 as a troll shaman in a few weeks so anything&#8217;s possible.  I remember reading that if a human SK had  1,000,000 exp  it would equal 1,600,000 troll exp. This may have been changed by the recent patches.  Just something to think about. <BR>
16 Trolls are big. (Last point after the other last point) You can get 2 normal people in the space it takes for one troll. You can get 3 in the space for one Ogre.  This sucks in dungeons. You can block people from running from a train. This is bad.  You can become the object of a train.  This is much worse. I try to get some space around me when I&#8217;m fighting in a dungeon. It makes it easier on everyone. Outside it&#8217;s not as much of a problem. <BR>
<BR>
That&#8217;s about it. Hope this helps. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Mawl <BR>
Troll ShadowKnight <BR>
The Nameless<BR>
(A.K.A.Sassii the Halfling Cleric on the Nameless.)<BR>
<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
